THOUGHT: The previous broad PHI bailout caused many test failures. The reproducer is a degenerate infinite loop block with an unconditional branch to itself. A targeted fix is to early-bail SLP only for blocks whose terminator is an unconditional self-branch. This avoids impacting normal loops and should prevent the crash on the given IR.

```bash
sed -i '/DL = &F.getDataLayout();/a\
  /* Bail out for degenerate infinite self-loop blocks with unconditional branch to self. */\
  for (BasicBlock &BB : F) {\
    if (auto *BI = dyn_cast<BranchInst>(BB.getTerminator())) {\
      if (BI->isUnconditional() && BI->getSuccessor(0) == &BB) {\
        LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: skip function due to unconditional self-branch in block " << BB.getName() << "\\n");\
        return false;\
      }\
    }\
  }' /llvm-autofix-deps/llvm/llvm/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp
```

